 234:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c **** 
 235:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     [..]
 236:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     For specific DFSDM filter analog watchdog callback use dedicated unregister callback:
 237:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     HAL_DFSDM_Filter_UnRegisterAwdCallback().
 238:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c **** 
 239:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     [..]
 240:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     By default, after the call of init function and if the state is RESET
 241:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak functions:
 242:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     examples HAL_DFSDM_ChannelScdCallback(), HAL_DFSDM_FilterErrorCallback().
 243:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 244:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     reset to the legacy weak functions in the init and de-init only when these
 245:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 246:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the init and de-init keep and use
 247:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 248:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c **** 
 249:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     [..]
 250:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 251:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 252:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 253:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     during the init/de-init.
 254:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks using
 255:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     HAL_DFSDM_Channel_RegisterCallback() or
 256:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     HAL_DFSDM_Filter_RegisterCallback() before calling init or de-init function.
 257:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c **** 
 258:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dfsdm.c ****     [..]
